A 2010 study in the Journal of Mental Health
Addiction found both lights and music created

00:00:38.010 --> 00:00:39.859
"increased arousal" effects.

00:00:39.859 --> 00:00:43.900
And a new study in the Journal of Neuroscience
looked at the brains of rats finding increased

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:49.390
arousal increases dopamine reception -- one
